Name: Aquatic Vegetation
Description: Plants normally found growing in the water column, either partially or totally submerged.

Name: Benthic Macroinvertebrates
Description: Invertebrate animals inhabiting the bottom of a water body.

Name: Birds
Description: Warm-blooded egg-laying animals possessing feathers, wings, and a beak.

Name: Corals
Description: Hard stony substance secreted by certain marine coelenterates as an external skeleton, typically forming large reefs in warm seas.

Name: Fish/Nekton
Description: Fish or other animals inhabiting the water column between the surface and the bottom.

Name: Fungi
Description: Unicellular, multicellular, or syncytial spore-producing organisms feeding on organic matter, including molds, yeast, mushrooms, and toadstools.

Name: Invertebrates
Description: Invertebrate animals are without a vertebral column or lacking backbone/spinal column

Name: Periphyton
Description: Near-microscopic plant material found attached to solid surfaces submerged in the aquatic environment.

Name: Phytoplankton/Zooplankton
Description: Near-microscopic plants and animals found in the water column between the surface and the bottom.

Name: Terrestrial Vegetation
Description: Plants normally found growing out of water.  Trees, shrubs, grasses, etc.
